<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/2267: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-28T17:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">December 28,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>544. B–818. Our B–816.<note n="31" xml:id="d156fn31"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note> In final text of decision given
                            interpretation word “default” paragraph 17, annex 2, reference to
                            paragraph 18, same annex, is deleted and “default” is simply defined as
                            signifying “voluntary default.” Boyden.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
